author: The Journal-Standard
title: Prep Football Roundup: Stockton denies Ashton-Franklin Center a playoff berth
text: Posted Oct. 23, 2015 at 10:58 PM Updated at 10:58 PM By The Journal-Standard Posted Oct. 23, 2015 at 10:58 PM STOCKTON â€” Ashton-Franklin Center needed a victory in Friday's regular-season finale to be playoff eligible. And the Raiders came out strong against Stockton. But Jacob Hilliker's 33-yard run early in the first quarter wasn't enough, as Stockton responded with 54 unaswered points to roll to the 54-6 victory. Trailing 6-0, Hayden Fox hit Gavin Krahmer on a 44-yard TD pass to put the Blackhawks up 8-6. Hayden Hayes added a 4-yard TD run and Dillon Hatfield scored from 11 yards out to make it 24-6 at the half. Luke Huschitt (9 yards), Aaron Dvorak (2 yards) and Thomas Eden (2-yards) each added rushing touchdowns in the third quarter, and Connor Davis capped things in the fourth when he returned a fumble 47 yards for Stockton. Hayes led the Blackhawks with 80 yards rushing on 12 carries, while Jake Hageman topped AFC with 96 yards on 19 rushes. braden Staver led the Stockton defense wth 11 tackes, whiel Chad Larson had 8. Dalton Ibarra topped AFC with 12. By The Journal-Standard
